org.eclipse.wst.jsdt.core.dom

Class ModuleSpecifier

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.wst.jsdt.core.dom.ASTNode
      • org.eclipse.wst.jsdt.core.dom.ModuleSpecifier

  • public class ModuleSpecifier
extends ASTNode
    ModuleSpecifier for Import/Export declarations

    When used with ImportDeclaration The discoverableName refers to the name of the export imported from the module. The local refers to the binding imported into the local module scope. For basic named import such as import {foo} from "mod" discoverableName and local are equivalent nodes.

    isDefault is used with ImportDeclaration to signal a default import such as import foo from "mod.js".

    namespace is used with imports to signal a namespace import e.g., * as foo in import * as foo from "mod.js".

    Provisional API: This class/interface is part of an interim API that is still under development and expected to change significantly before reaching stability. It is being made available at this early stage to solicit feedback from pioneering adopters on the understanding that any code that uses this API will almost certainly be broken (repeatedly) as the API evolves.
